9.18.19  3:27 pm   i want to create my own superquit button with keyboard maestro or something and i was wondering, does yours force quit apps or saves everything and quits normally? thanks :)

      it uses 'quit all other applications', but for textedit specifically it has an elaborate mechanism to save every un-named open file to a file named scrap20190919071048 (based on the date/time), and for various other programs i have save procedures that make more sense for those cases. also it has 'close all windows' in finder, and i've found i have to add quite a bit of alternating and checking, but at this point it's extremely solid, and it actually keeps checking to see if it's done early and sends the victory bong if it's done already. there is a victory bong. it will need to constantly be evolving as other programs and save-situations become relevant. i can give you more details if you contact me
